definitions.definition: Related to the paying of tribute .
Yielding supplies of any kind; serving to form or make up, a greater object of the same kind, as a part, branch, etc.; contributing.
examples: The Ohio has many tributary streams, and is itself tributary to the Mississippi.

main_definition: Related to the paying of tribute .
